            <p><add hand="#barker">Assuring him of Austin's welfare </add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p><placeName>Bexar</placeName>, <date when="1835-08-04">4th August 1835</date></p>
<p><persName>James F. Perry Esq</persName></p>
<p>Dear Sir,</p>
<p>Immediately on my arrival here I made enquiries after our <persName>mutual
friend</persName> <persName>Col. Austin</persName> and learned from <persName>Col. Ugartechea</persName> that he is still in
<placeName>Mexico</placeName>, doing well and at liberty. An <persName>Officer </persName>is here who lately left that
<placeName>capital </placeName>and brings the intelligence, I shall therefore endeavour to find
him out and will transmit to you further particulars Being much occupied
I have no time for more than to Subscribe myself</p>
<p><persName>Edward Gritten</persName> [Rubric]</p>
<p>[Addressed:] <persName>James F. Perry Esq.</persName> <placeName>San Felipe de Austin</placeName></p>



        </div1>
